    pearls: ["Water follows sodium: hyponatremia causes cellular swelling (cerebral edema risk); hypernatremia causes cellular shrinkage (neurological dysfunction)","The body compensates for potassium-hydrogen ion exchange: acidosis pushes potassium out of cells (pseudohyperkalemia); alkalosis pulls potassium into cells (hypokalemia)","Magnesium must be corrected before calcium and potassium will correct; refractory hypokalemia or hypocalcemia often has underlying hypomagnesemia","Correcting hyponatremia too rapidly (more than 8-12 mEq/L in 24 hours) can cause osmotic demyelination syndrome — irreversible neurological damage","Calcium gluconate for hyperkalemia does NOT lower potassium; it stabilizes the cardiac membrane while other treatments (insulin + glucose, albuterol, kayexalate) shift or remove potassium","Daily weight is the single most reliable indicator of fluid balance: 1 kg change equals approximately 1 liter of fluid gained or lost"],
