      action: "Inhibits mycolic acid synthesis in the mycobacterial cell wall, bactericidal against actively growing Mycobacterium tuberculosis",
      sideEffects: "Hepatotoxicity (monitor LFTs monthly), peripheral neuropathy (prevented with pyridoxine/vitamin B6 supplementation), drug-induced lupus, optic neuritis",
      contra: "Active hepatic disease or history of INH-associated hepatitis; concurrent use of hepatotoxic drugs; caution in alcohol use disorder",
      pearl: "Always co-administer pyridoxine (vitamin B6) 25-50 mg daily to prevent peripheral neuropathy; instruct patients to report signs of hepatotoxicity (jaundice, dark urine, abdominal pain, nausea); avoid alcohol during therapy"
