      name: "Oral Nutritional Supplements (protein-enriched formulas)",
      type: "Medical nutritional therapy",
      action: "Provides concentrated calories, protein (typically 15-20g per serving), and micronutrients to combat malnutrition and support muscle protein synthesis in frail elderly with inadequate oral intake",
      sideEffects: "GI bloating, diarrhea, early satiety (may reduce meal intake if given too close to meals), hyperglycemia in diabetic patients",
      contra: "Severe GI obstruction; adjust formulation for renal impairment (low potassium/phosphorus), hepatic impairment (BCAA-enriched), or diabetes (low glycemic index formulas)",
